text.section:
A property tax credit provided for under this section shall:
be subject to eligibility requirements no less stringent than those applicable to credits authorized under § 9-204 of this subtitle;
be for a period that does not exceed 10 years for each property;
apply to eligible improvements which are:
located within the boundaries of:
a property listed individually on the National Register of Historic Places, or a national register historic or landmark district;
a property or district designated as a historic property or district under local law; or
a property included within the boundaries of a certified heritage area under § 13-1111 of the Financial Institutions Article; and
for a property or district under paragraph (3)(i)1 or 2 of this subsection, determined by the local historic district commission to be compatible with local historic preservation standards.
